%20courtroom%20battle%20that%20followed%2C%20spearheaded%20by%20a%20man%20of%20unshakeable%20convictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch1%3EThe%20Man%20Behind%20The%20'Legend'%3C%2Fh1%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201857%20in%20Mankara%2C%20a%20village%20in%20Kerala's%20Palakkad%20district%2C%20Sir%20Chettur%20Sankaran%20Nair%20hailed%20from%20an%20aristocratic%20lineage%20with%20close%20associations%20to%20the%20East%20India%20Company.%20His%20early%20education%20led%20him%20to%20Presidency%20College%2C%20Madras%2C%20where%20he%20was%20drawn%20to%20the%20field%20of%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20began%20his%20legal%20career%20in%201880%20at%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Madras%20under%20the%20mentorship%20of%20Sir%20Horatio%20Shepherd%2C%20who%20would%20later%20become%20Chief%20Justice.%20Nair's%20brilliance%20and%20fierce%20independence%20quickly%20became%20evident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fcdep2mfk_chettur-sankaran-nair_625x300_11_April_25.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20his%20legal%20career%2C%20Nair%20was%20known%20for%20his%20refusal%20to%20conform.%20Early%20on%2C%20he%20opposed%20a%20resolution%20passed%20by%20Indian%20vakils%20(lawyers)%20of%20Madras%20that%20discouraged%20working%20under%20English%20barristers.%20For%20Nair%2C%20professional%20choices%20should%20be%20governed%20by%20merit%20and%20client%20interest%2C%20not%20nationalism%20or%20peer%20pressure.%20His%20stand%20led%20to%20his%20boycott%20by%20fellow%20lawyers%2C%20but%20he%20remained%20undeterred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENair%20was%20appointed%20Advocate-General%20and%20later%20became%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Madras%20High%20Court.%20His%20judicial%20tenure%20was%20marked%20by%20bold%20judgments%20upholding%20inter-caste%20and%20inter-religious%20marriages%2C%20as%20well%20as%20rulings%20that%20challenged%20the%20rigid%20orthodoxy%20of%20caste-based%20discrimination.%20His%201914%20ruling%20in%20Budasna%20v%20Fatima%2C%20where%20he%20held%20that%20converts%20to%20Hinduism%20could%20not%20be%20considered%20outcastes%2C%20remains%20a%20landmark%20judgment%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch1%3EPolitical%20Ascendancy%20And%20Reform%3C%2Fh1%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201897%2C%20he%20became%20the%20youngest%20president%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20at%20the%20time%20and%20the%20only%20Malayali%20to%20hold%20the%20position.%20Nair%20was%20not%20afraid%20to%20ruffle%20feathers%20-%20be%20it%20among%20the%20Anglo-Indian%20elite%2C%20the%20Brahmin%20establishment%2C%20or%20the%20British%20authorities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22File%20photo%20of%20Chettur%20Sankaran%20Nair%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22File%20photo%20of%20Chettur%20Sankaran%20Nair%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fj88k4sio_chettur-sankaran-nair_625x300_11_April_25.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFile%20photo%20of%20Chettur%20Sankaran%20Nair%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20participated%20in%20the%20Montagu-Chelmsford%20reforms%20and%20advocated%20for%20increasing%20Indian%20participation%20in%20governance.%20By%201915%2C%20he%20was%20inducted%20into%20the%20Viceroy's%20Executive%20Council%2C%20overseeing%20the%20education%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Nair's%20political%20ideology%20was%20as%20nuanced%20as%20his%20legal%20career.%20While%20he%20believed%20in%20constitutional%20reform%2C%20he%20was%20critical%20of%20certain%20aspects%20of%20Gandhi's%20political%20methods%2C%20particularly%20civil%20disobedience.%20This%20ideological%20divergence%20would%20later%20find%20expression%20in%20his%20controversial%20book%20Gandhi%20and%20Anarchy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch1%3EJallianwala%20Bagh%20Massacre%20-%20The%20Turning%20Point%3C%2Fh1%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2013%2C%201919%2C%20British%20Brigadier%20General%20Reginald%20Dyer%20ordered%20troops%20to%20open%20fire%20on%20a%20peaceful%20gathering%20in%20Amritsar's%20Jallianwala%20Bagh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHundreds%20of%20unarmed%20civilians%2C%20including%20women%20and%20children%2C%20were%20mercilessly%20gunned%20down.%20The%20massacre%20became%20a%20watershed%20moment%20in%20India's%20freedom%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Kesari%20Chapter%202%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Kesari%20Chapter%202%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fhkd75vl_s_625x300_11_April_25.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20still%20from%20Kesari%20Chapter%202%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Nair%20was%20the%20only%20Indian%20member%20of%20the%20Viceroy's%20Executive%20Council.%20Appalled%20by%20the%20government's%20justification%20of%20the%20massacre%2C%20he%20resigned%20in%20protest%20-%20a%20move%20unprecedented%20for%20its%20sheer%20audacity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20resignation%20sent%20shockwaves%20through%20the%20colonial%20administration%20and%20lent%20weight%20to%20nationalist%20sentiments%20across%20the%20country.%20It%20also%20led%20to%20the%20removal%20of%20martial%20law%20in%20Punjab%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20committee%20under%20Lord%20William%20Hunter%20to%20investigate%20the%20massacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch1%3EThe%20Courtroom%20Battle%20That%20Shook%20The%20Empire%3C%2Fh1%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201922%2C%20Nair%20published%20%3Cem%3EGandhi%20and%20Anarchy%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20he%20criticised%20British%20colonial%20rule%20and%20laid%20blame%20on%20Michael%20O'Dwyer%2C%20the%20then-Lieutenant%20Governor%20of%20Punjab%2C%20for%20the%20atrocities%20at%20Jallianwala%20Bagh.%20Infuriated%2C%20O'Dwyer%20sued%20Nair%20for%20