arder%20to%20find%20a%20steady%20job%20in%20television%20so%20I%20took%20a%20position%20in%20podcasting.%20I%20was%20there%20a%20little%20over%20a%20year%20but%20left%20when%20things%20went%20south%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20declared%20bankruptcy%20a%20few%20months%20later.%20I%20was%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpregnant-40-still-dont-feel-grown-up-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enewly%20pregnant%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20look%20for%20a%20new%20full-time%20job%20while%20pregnant.%20Becoming%20a%20sitcom%20writer%20had%20been%20an%20uphill%20battle%20and%20one%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20give%20up.%20I%20took%20a%20few%20short-term%20contract%20positions%2C%20and%20after%20giving%20birth%20to%20my%20son%2C%20I%20wasn't%20working%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20finally%20started%20to%20consider%20working%20again%2C%20there'd%20been%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20podcasting%20openings%20I%20found%20%E2%80%94%20many%20producer%20roles%20also%20required%20editing%20experience%2C%20which%20wasn't%20a%20skill%20I%20had%20or%20was%20interested%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2223c4b75d-f43b-4fbb-afd7-4ab69ee5bc62%5C%22%3ESince%20becoming%20a%20mother%2C%20I%20can't%20seem%20to%20find%20a%20career%20path%20that%20excites%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20self-admitted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-tips-for-changing-careers-finding-fulfilling-work-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20soul%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20a%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20still%20look%20for%20jobs%20and%20often%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20I%20really%20think%20about%20what%20it%20would%20mean%20to%20take%20any%20of%20the%20jobs%20I%20apply%20for%2C%20sadness%20washes%20over%20me%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20being%20away%20from%20my%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20it's%20time%20to%20accept%20what%20I%20do%20feel%20passionate%20about%3A%20my%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20if%20I%20returned%20to%20work%20I%20would%20need%20to%20find%20childcare%20since%20a%20day%20job%20would%20likely%20go%20to%205%20p.m.%20and%20my%20son%20is%20out%20of%20preschool%20by%203%20p.m.%20Plus%2C%20my%20son%20only%20goes%20to%20preschool%20three%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it's%20day%20care%20or%20a%20nanny%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-childcare-costs-in-us-women-workforce-cheapest-countries-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eamount%20of%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20would%20cost%20makes%20taking%20any%20job%20less%20appealing.%20It's%20just%20not%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20a%20clear%20career%20trajectory%2C%20it%20might%20be%20a%20different%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d0bb5ee-6d41-424e-a7c5-5ccdccbc939b%5C%22%3EI%20was%20surprised%20that%20I%20enjoy%20being%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20with%20my%20son%20every%20single%20day%20until%20he%20started%20preschool%20at%201%20%C2%BD%20years%20old.%20I%20was%20there%20for%20all%20the%20milestones%3A%20first%20word%2C%20steps%2C%20giggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20amazed%20at%20how%20this%20helpless%20being%20transformed%20into%20a%20chatty%20toddler%2C%20full%20of%20personality%2C%20right%20before%20my%20eyes.%20Though%20clich%C3%A9%2C%20it%20was%20true%3A%20The%20days%20are%20long%20but%20the%20years%20are%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20some%20days%20are%20just%20hard.%20His%20naps%20offer%20me%20a%20much-needed%20break%20but%20then%20sometimes%20they%20don't%20happen.%20Food%20gets%20thrown%20on%20the%20just-washed%20floor.%20If%20he%20doesn't%20have%20a%20cold%2C%20then%20he%20has%20a%20stomach%20bug.%20It%20feels%20like%20a%20week%20without%20an%20illness%20is%20a%20rarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20now%20that's%20he%20in%20school%20part%20time%2C%20my%20hours%20alone%20fly%20by%2C%20and%20I%20never%20accomplish%20all%20the%20to-dos%20I%20hope%20to.%20At%203%20p.m.%20I%20switch%20back%20to%20mom%20duty%20and%20I%20must%20entertain%20him%2C%20keep%20him%20away%20from%20the%20remote%20(although%20sometimes%20you%20just%20have%20to%20put%20on%20the%20TV)%2C%20and%20manage%20his%20multistep%20bedtime%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20all%20the%20trying%20moments%2C%20I've%20realized%20I'm%20the%20happiest%20I've%20ever%20been.%20My%20son%20makes%20me%20laugh%20constantly%2C%20and%20I%20can't%20tell%20him%20enough%20how%20much%20I%20love%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20privileged%20that%20my%20family%20can%20afford%20to%20live%20on%20my%20husband's%20salary%20alone.%20An%20additional%20salary%20would%20certainly%20be%20helpful%2C%20but%20the%20opportunity%20cost%20of%20me%20finding%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20spending%20my%20days%20with%20my%20son%20%E2%80%94%20is%20too%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20name%20may%20not%20be%20in%20the%20credits%20of%20your%20favorite%20comedy%20show%2C%20but%20I%20know%20people%20whose%20names%20are%20and%20I%20wouldn't%20trade%20places%20with%20any%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20my%20days%20may%20not%20be%20glamorous%20and%20are%20often%20monotonous%2C%20I%20love%20my%20life%20as%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnever-wanted-stay-at-home-mom-surprised-i-love-it-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744367821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eeb6f9b8b41a9673fc8f53%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnever-wanted-stay-at-home-mom-surprised-i-love-it-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dyana%20Lederman%20moved%20to%20LA%20as%20an%20aspiring%20Hollywood%20sitcom%20writer.%20She%20judged%20stat-at-home%20moms%20and%20never%20wanted%20to%20be%20one.%20Then%20she%20got%20pregnant.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Dyana%20Lederman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%